    class CellButton
extends javafx.scene.control.Button
implements java.lang.Comparable<CellButton>
    This class provides the individual "cells" for the game grid. Extends the JavaFX Button class.

    • Method Detail

      • wrapCoordinate

        private static int wrapCoordinate(int c,
                                  int gridSize)
        Computes coordinates which wrap around the edges of the grid. Used to compute the list of a cell's neighbours.
        Parameters:
        c - the coordinate
        gridSize - the dimension of the grid
        Returns:
        if c is -1, returns grid size, and if c is equal to the grid size, returns 0. (i.e. the grid wraps around from top to bottom, left to right, and vice versa

      • getCellSize

        static double getCellSize()

      • getNeighbours

        private java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Integer> getNeighbours(int gridSize)
        Creates a list of the cell's eight neighbours at construction time, rather than on each grid iteration. This improves the runGame() method's performance significantly.
        Parameters:
        gridSize - the grid size parameter is passed to the wrapCoordinates() helper.
        Returns:
        a list of the cell's neighbours.

      • reverseState

        void reverseState()
        Reverses the state of the cell. If the cell is off, it will be set to on and its colour changed appropriately, and vice versa.
